<br>
Idealists seem to think this way- that somehow their conversation on a message board or in a coffee shop represents an accurate crossection of the player base. Actually, it is misleading at best. This stuff represents the thoughts and opinions of people that like to post on message boards. It is foolish to assume that we speak for the majority of players on any server.<br>
<br>
People that havent come to FV because of the 1 character limit will flood in now, knowing they can twink, and the impulse to make an anonymous character to just annoy people might be too tempting for the people that don't have the self-control of an 'enlightened roleplayer'.<br>
<br>
Most peope on this message board will claim they are roleplayers. But every time I play, I see about 1 in 10 people that barely talk, let alone roleplay or respond to my RP. <br>
<br>
Taking this illusion into account, and adding my own experience with the player-base online, I'd have to say that adding another character slot would drastically change, if not ruin the entire purpose of the FV server. They might as well drop the language barrier too, and just make it a blue server where some of the roleplayers tend to hang out.<br>
